q
/Tx BMC 
q
1 1 492.3312 306.999 re
W
BT
/HeBo 9.0 Tf 0 g
2 297.999 Td
(The suspicious activity involving Acme LLC was identified on August 18, 2023, through an alert generated by the bank's monitoring system, which indicated unusual cash patterns and multiple day deposits. Between January 15, 2024, and January 22, 2024, the subject conducted three cash deposits totaling $15,500, with each transaction structured to remain below the Currency Transaction Report \(CTR\) threshold. Specifically, the transactions included a deposit of $4,800 on January 15, 2024, followed by a deposit of $5,200 on January 17, 2024, and a funds transfer of $5,500 on January 20, 2024, to a new external account. The cumulative amount involved in these transactions raised concerns of potential money laundering due to the structured nature of the deposits and the lack of a clear lawful purpose. Supporting documentation includes transaction records for each deposit and transfer, which are retained by Example Community Bank in New York, NC. Notably, the subject declined to provide an explanation for the large cash deposits when approached by bank personnel. The bank has not yet contacted law enforcement regarding this matter, but further investigation is recommended to determine the legitimacy of the transactions and the overall business operations of Acme LLC.) Tj
ET
Q
EMC
Q

endstream
